      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must pass published benchmark verification cases relevant to rotating turbomachinery flows at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent has been verified against the ASME V&V 20 lid-driven cavity and backward-facing step benchmarks. Published verification reports confirm correct implementation of the governing equations for the flow regime of interest."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be computed across at least three systematically refined meshes with GCI < 5% on the primary QoI (relative hemolysis index) to satisfy MRL 2 requirements at the elevated consequence level.",
      "rationale": "Mesh sensitivity was evaluated using only two mesh densities (2.1 M and 4.3 M cells). Richardson extrapolation and formal GCI computation were not performed. The coarser mesh shows a 12% deviation in predicted hemolysis index relative to the finer mesh, and no extrapolated reference solution is available. The achieved level of discretization error control does not meet the required level for this decision consequence."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
